Time-stop
- time-stop is a period of time in which time-dependent mechanics stop experiencing time
    - regeneration stops
    - recovery stops
- game-time dependent mechanics are:
    - skill point recovery
    - enemy stagger recovery
    - enemy stagger break
- real-time dependent mechanics are:
    - any cooldowns
- mechanic with time-stops
    - ultimate skill animation
    - combo skill
    - perfect dodge
    - enemy node stagger break
    - enemy full stagger break
    - [ignore] enemy red bubble charging interrupt
- interactions with other time-stop periods
    - all time-stops can start within dodge's time-stop period
    - combo time-stops can start within all time-stop periods except for ultimate animation time-stop
    - ultimate time-stops can start within all time-stop periods except for other ultimate animation time-stops
    - most time-stops can interrupt each other, meaning if two time-stops overlap in time, the older time-stop will prematurely end, and the newer time-stop will take effect
        - ultimate animation time-stop can interrupt all other time-stops except for ultimate
        - combo (time-stop) interrupts combo (time-stop)
        - combo interrupts dodge
        - combo interrupts stagger
        - stagger interrupts dodge
- interactions with events
    - event overlapping with time-stop periods caused by another event will experience time-stop effects
        - one effect is that the event duration will be extended by the duration of the time-stop experienced
        - if the time-stop is interrupted, the event is extended by only the partial duration up until the interruption
    - an event with a time-stop event will not extend its own duration
